      "name": "Hemolysis index comparison — clinical circuit observational data",
      "description": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) predicted by the CFD model was compared against values extracted from a retrospective observational study of 47 CPB circuits operated at five flow-speed combinations matching the COU envelope. Mean RH_predicted / RH_observed ratios ranged from 0.82 to 1.09 across all operating points, with all predictions satisfying RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. The observational dataset spans three clinical sites and two pump generations, providing broad coverage of the intended operating space. The study team notes that the breadth of the observational data provides a rigorous basis for model acceptance, as the range of real-world conditions encountered exceeds what any single bench experiment could achieve. Accordingly, the validation team concluded that the evidence is sufficient to support model credibility at MRL 2.",
